Voici le **script Python** pour générer dynamiquement un fichier `.scss` à partir des métriques extraites (typos, couleurs, espacements, etc.). Ce script est à placer par exemple dans `design_generation/generators/generate_scss_from_metrics.py` :

---

### 📄 `generate_scss_from_metrics.py`

```python
# :name: generate_scss_from_metrics.py
# :description: Génère un fichier SCSS à partir des métriques de style extraites d'un site scrappé
# :input: site_name (str), metrics (dict), output_dir (str)
# :output: chemin du fichier SCSS généré
# :tags: scss, generation, style, automation

import os

def generate_scss_from_metrics(site_name, metrics, output_dir="design_generation/generated_scss"):
    """
    Génère un fichier SCSS de base à partir des données extraites
    """

    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
    filepath = os.path.join(output_dir, f"{site_name}.scss")

    font_family = metrics.get("fonts", ["sans-serif"])[0]
    font_size = metrics.get("font_sizes", ["16px"])[0]
    line_height = metrics.get("line_heights", ["1.5"])[0]
    color_primary = metrics.get("colors", ["#000000"])[0]
    color_secondary = metrics.get("colors", ["#ffffff"])[1] if len(metrics.get("colors", [])) > 1 else "#ffffff"
    spacing = metrics.get("spacings", ["1rem"])[0]
    border_radius = metrics.get("border_radius", ["4px"])[0]

    with open(filepath, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        f.write(f"""// SCSS generated for {site_name}
$font-family: {font_family};
$font-size: {font_size};
$line-height: {line_height};
$color-primary: {color_primary};
$color-secondary: {color_secondary};
$spacing: {spacing};
$border-radius: {border_radius};

body {{
  font-family: $font-family;
  font-size: $font-size;
  line-height: $line-height;
  color: $color-primary;
  background-color: $color-secondary;
  padding: $spacing;
}}
""")

    return filepath
```

